Characteristics that an intra-organizational application should have
There are various [workflows] in the organization: "Individual A applies, and another individual B approves.

	Can Individual A check the progress status of the workflow?
	Can you view past workflows?
	Can searches be performed against the workflow?
	Can the workflow be shared with information other than those involved in the workflow?
	Can you communicate electronically about individual workflows?
		Issues when discussed in venues not set up with workflow (e.g., chat, verbal, etc.):.
			When you look back on it later, you don't know "why that decision was made".
		Important to have a set of workflows and communication venues.